  "body": "### Component\n\nFoundryup\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n1. ConflictLock\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/5577fcb7d92ef4f3bdb81544e1ed1e6cb402fa86/evm/src/executor/fork/cache.rs#L181-L183\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/5577fcb7d92ef4f3bdb81544e1ed1e6cb402fa86/evm/src/executor/fork/cache.rs#L219-L222\r\nThe lock orders of storage and accounts conflict between do_commit and clone. When interleaved as the table, a deadlock will happen.\r\n\r\n2. DoubleLock\r\n`arc_state: parking_lot::RwLock<...>`\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/5577fcb7d92ef4f3bdb81544e1ed1e6cb402fa86/evm/src/fuzz/strategies/param.rs#L58-L67\r\nThe two locks are on L60 and L67.\r\nThere is a double read lock on arc_state in fuzz_param_from_state, if interleaved by a write from another thread, then a deadlock will happen.\r\n",
